messages.content: You are tasked with creating a structured output from the provided user message.

Full path
- /api/orders/mine

All methods acceptable
- false

HTTP methods (based on the code)
- HEAD: false
- POST: false
- OPTIONS: false
- TRACE: false
- GET: true
- PUT: false
- DELETE: false
- PATCH: false

Explanation
- server.js mounts the order router at the prefix /api/orders: app.use('/api/orders', orderRoutes).
- In routes/orderRoutes.js the route handling the controller getMyOrders is defined as router.route('/mine').get(protect, getMyOrders);. Combined with the mounted prefix this yields /api/orders/mine.
- The controller file contains a comment saying GET /api/orders/myorders, but that is outdated/incorrect; the actual registered path is /mine, so the correct full path is /api/orders/mine.
- Only a .get(...) handler is registered for that path in the router, so only GET is acceptable according to the code. No explicit handlers for HEAD, POST, OPTIONS, TRACE, PUT, DELETE, or PATCH are registered for this route, so they are not considered acceptable based on the code alone.
